<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 6:29PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Gratiot
and southeastern Isabella Counties through 715 PM EDT...
At 628 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mount Pleasant, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant...      Alma...                St. Louis...
Shepherd...            Breckenridge...        Forest Hill...
Delwin...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
